      "href": "/cultclass1c/list/coquette/",
      "user": "cultclass1c",
      "slug": "coquette",
      "title": "Coquette",
      "desc": "Beautiful and tragic, the coquette style celebrates the hyper femme with pastel colours, ruffles and bows. It nods to a youthful nostalgia while being cognizant of its flirtatious allure. \n\nA line can be traced from the underage and overtly sexualised eponymous Lolita from Nabokov's controversial 1955 book through to current day 'coquette' media. Whilst veering away from the more shocking and controversial aspects of the original, media often displays beautiful, hyper-femme women shrouded in mystique, desired from afar, with ultimately their stories ending in tragedy.\n\nWith this list and my following discussion on Youtube, I intend to explore;\n-the word coquette as it derives from the French\n-beautiful female tragedy, death in ruffles, the line between the tumblr sad girl… more",
      "owner": "List by rebecca dr PATRON",
